cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on network functions virtualization and virtualization techniques used in IP multimedia subsystem (IMS) cloud computing to develop different networking functions. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a virtual load balanced call admission controller for cloud-hosted SIP servers, which involves distributed computing and resource allocation. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a linear programming model to determine the optimal call admission rates and signaling paths for admitted calls along with the optimal allocation of CPU and memory resources of the SIP servers, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The proposed scheme is implemented in smart applications on virtual infrastructure (SAVI), which involves computational engineering. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new linear programming model, which involves algorithms and optimization techniques.
